{
  "texts": [
    "The active circles correspond to the exponents of the connection in the Levelt-Turrittin normal form, and the monodromy of V 0 is usually called the formal monodromy.",
    "In particular, a connection is regular if and only if its only active circle is the tame circle ⟨0⟩.",
    "A useful observation is that one can equivalently view an I-graded local system V 0 → ∂ as a local system on (the étalé space of) I, i.e.",
    "there exists a local system on V 0 on I such that",
    "If ⟨q⟩ is a circle of ramification r, when going once around ⟨q⟩ we go r times around ∂."
  ]
}